-- 
French Foreign Ministry Criticizes Syrian Crackdown on Protests

-- B y   G r e g o r y   V i s c u s i
-- 
2011-03-21T12:51:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/french-foreign-ministry-criticizes-syrian-crackdown-on-protests.html
The French government condemned the
crackdown on protesters in a southern Syrian town that resulted
in deaths over the weekend.    France  condemns the violence that led to several deaths
and numerous wounded among demonstrators gathered Friday,
Saturday and Sunday in Deraa,” a Foreign Ministry spokesman,  Bernard Valero , said an e-mailed statement. France “repeats its
attachment to the right in all countries to protest
peacefully.”  Valero called on the Syrian government to release all
political prisoners and live up to human rights agreements that
it’s signed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gregory Viscusi in Paris at 
 gviscusi@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at 
 jhertling@bloomberg.net  